18/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- US and Romanian officials are conducting negotiations on the deployment of US military bases in Romania, Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu said Tuesday (17 May), adding that an agreement is expected by the end of the month.
Talks focused on the financing needed to build the bases and on each side's obligations, he said.
The United States recently announced plans to move small mobile facilities to Romania and Bulgaria as part of a process designed to adapt its military to new challenges.
(AP - 17/05/05)
